KEY
----
A <- Node
B <- Bridge node/Gate node
R <- Actual Router
C <- Non-mesh node in the same subnet (Connected to R)
O <- Outside network
=> <- Ping
<=> <- Ping both ways
(wr) <- without router


------------------------------------------------------------


* B <=> A (wr)
* B <=> C 
* A => R
* B => R
* A <=> C  
* B => O 
* A => O
Resumes after R goes down and comes back, no need to reconfigure

